SUMMARY:NJYC: The Vocal Edge Festival
DESCRIPTION:NJYC: The Vocal Edge Festival\nApril 18\, 2026 at 4:00 p.m.\nChatham United Methodist Church\, Chatham\nFREE Event | Advanced registration required for participants\nClick HERE to register \nDesigned for boys in grades 5–8\, this one-day choir festival welcomes both individual participants and school or community ensembles. Working with guest clinician Dr. Brandon Williams\, singers will explore repertoire and techniques appropriate for changing voices in a supportive\, engaging environment. The Festival begins at 10:00 a.m. and concludes with a public concert at 4:00 p.m.
URL:https://whartonarts.org/calendar/njyc-the-vocal-edge-festival/
LOCATION:Chatham United Methodist Church\, 460 Main St\, Chatham\, New Jersey\, 07928\, United States
CATEGORIES:NJYC,Wharton
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://whartonarts.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Untitled-4-x-6-in-scaled.png
END:VEVENT
