SUMMARY:NJYC: Spring Concert
DESCRIPTION:NJYC: Spring Concert\nMay 17\, 2026 at 4:00 p.m.\n$20/Adults\, $15/Students & Seniors\nNicholas Music Center at Rutgers University\, New Brunswick\nClick HERE for tickets \nNJYC Primo Coro\, Coriste: Trish Joyce\, Director\nNJYC Cor Amici\, Camerata: Dan Malloy\, Director\nNJYC Sola Voce: Joanna Scarangello\, Director\nAccompanists: Phillip Steffani\, Andrew Macirowski\, and Leah Frank \nCelebrate spring with the New Jersey Youth Chorus as our young singers bring a fresh\, uplifting program to life. Featuring a mix of classical and contemporary repertoire\, this concert reflects the season’s spirit of growth\, joy\, and shared musical expression.
URL:https://whartonarts.org/calendar/spring-concert/
LOCATION:Nicholas Music Center at Rutgers New Brunswick\, 85 George St\, New Brunswick\, NJ\, 08901\, United States
CATEGORIES:NJYC,Wharton
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://whartonarts.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/i-2D7B824-X4.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Wharton Arts
X-SOURCE-URL:https://whartonarts.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T203000
DTSTAMP:20260406T230145
CREATED:20260126T203828Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260217T174200Z
UID:10000423-1777230000-1777235400@whartonarts.org
SUMMARY:NJYS Signature Concert: Voices of the North: Nordic & Baltic Soundscapes
DESCRIPTION:NJYS Signature Concert: Voices of the North: Nordic & Baltic Soundscapes\nApril 26\, 2026 at 7:00 p.m.\nNicholas Music Center at Rutgers University\, New Brunswick\n$20/Adults\, $15/Students & Seniors\nClick HERE for tickets \nNJYS Youth Symphony: Helen H. Cha-Pyo\, Conductor \nJourney into the sweeping soundscapes of Northern Europe as the NJYS Youth Symphony\, led by Helen Cha-Pyo\, brings to life the striking rhythmic force of Estonian composer Veljo Tormis’s Overture No. 2 and the majestic grandeur of American composer Howard Hanson\, whose Scandinavian heritage is celebrated in his Symphony No. 1 (“Nordic”). The program also features the 2026 NJYS Concerto Competition Winner\, showcasing one of the orchestra’s outstanding young soloists. \nThis concert serves as a powerful prelude to the Youth Symphony’s highly anticipated Summer 2026 tour to Finland and the Baltics\, offering audiences a glimpse into the musical landscapes and cultural connections that will shape the ensemble’s international journey. \n 
URL:https://whartonarts.org/calendar/njys-signature-concert-voices-of-the-north-nordic-baltic-soundscapes/
LOCATION:Nicholas Music Center at Rutgers New Brunswick\, 85 George St\, New Brunswick\, NJ\, 08901\, United States
CATEGORIES:NJYS,Wharton
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://whartonarts.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Photo-to-switch-for-April-26-YS-Concert.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="NJYS":MAILTO:info@NJYS.org
END:VEVENT
